EP.PMP.DESL.CD-transportation.def: Fuel prices refer to the pump prices of the most widely sold grade of diesel fuel. Prices have been converted from the local currency to U.S. dollars.
EP.PMP.DESL.CD-transportation.name: Pump price for diesel fuel

EP.PMP.SGAS.CD-transportation.def: Fuel prices refer to the pump prices of the most widely sold grade of gasoline. Prices have been converted from the local currency to U.S. dollars.
EP.PMP.SGAS.CD-transportation.name: Pump price for gasoline

IS.AIR.DPRT-transportation.def: Registered carrier departures worldwide are domestic takeoffs and takeoffs abroad of air carriers registered in the country.
IS.AIR.DPRT-transportation.name: Air transport
IS.AIR.DPRT-transportation.source: International Civil Aviation Organization, Civil Aviation Statistics of the World and ICAO staff estimates.
IS.AIR.DPRT-transportation.dataset: International Civil Aviation Organization, Civil Aviation Statistics of the World and ICAO staff estimates.

IS.AIR.GOOD.MT.K1-transportation.def: Air freight is the volume of freight, express, and diplomatic bags carried on each flight stage (operation of an aircraft from takeoff to its next landing), measured in metric tons times kilometers traveled.
IS.AIR.GOOD.MT.K1-transportation.name: Air transport
IS.AIR.GOOD.MT.K1-transportation.source: International Civil Aviation Organization, Civil Aviation Statistics of the World and ICAO staff estimates.
IS.AIR.GOOD.MT.K1-transportation.dataset: International Civil Aviation Organization, Civil Aviation Statistics of the World and ICAO staff estimates.

IS.AIR.PSGR-transportation.def: Air passengers carried include both domestic and international aircraft passengers of air carriers registered in the country.
IS.AIR.PSGR-transportation.name: Air transport
IS.AIR.PSGR-transportation.source: International Civil Aviation Organization, Civil Aviation Statistics of the World and ICAO staff estimates.
IS.AIR.PSGR-transportation.dataset: International Civil Aviation Organization, Civil Aviation Statistics of the World and ICAO staff estimates.

IS.RRS.GOOD.MT.K6-transportation.def: Goods transported by railway are the volume of goods transported by railway, measured in metric tons times kilometers traveled.
IS.RRS.GOOD.MT.K6-transportation.name: Railways
IS.RRS.GOOD.MT.K6-transportation.source: Internation Union of Railways (UIC), OECD Statistics
IS.RRS.GOOD.MT.K6-transportation.dataset: Internation Union of Railways (UIC), OECD Statistics

IS.RRS.PASG.KM-transportation.def: Passengers carried by railway are the number of passengers transported by rail times kilometers traveled.
IS.RRS.PASG.KM-transportation.name: Railways
IS.RRS.PASG.KM-transportation.source: Internation Union of Railways (UIC), OECD Statistics
IS.RRS.PASG.KM-transportation.dataset: Internation Union of Railways (UIC), OECD Statistics

IS.RRS.TOTL.KM-transportation.def: Rail lines are the length of railway route available for train service, irrespective of the number of parallel tracks.
IS.RRS.TOTL.KM-transportation.name: Rail lines

IS.SHP.GCNW.XQ-transportation.def:
Liner Shipping Connectivity Index score indicates how well countries are connected to global shipping networks
based on the status of their maritime transport sector. The highest value in 2004 is 100.
IS.SHP.GCNW.XQ-transportation.name: Liner shipping connectivity index
IS.SHP.GCNW.XQ-transportation.source: United Nations Conference on Trade and Development, Review of Maritime Transport 2010.
IS.SHP.GCNW.XQ-transportation.dataset: United Nations Conference on Trade and Development, Review of Maritime Transport 2010.

IS.SHP.GOOD.TU-transportation.def: Port container traffic measures the flow of containers from land to sea transport modes., and vice versa, in twenty-foot equivalent units (TEUs), a standard-size container. Data refer to coastal shipping as well as international journeys. Transshipment traffic is counted as two lifts at the intermediate port (once to off-load and again as an outbound lift) and includes empty units.
IS.SHP.GOOD.TU-transportation.name: Container port traffic
